                                <date>1958</date>. С. <biblScope unit="page">??–??</biblScope>.</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><encodingDesc><tagsDecl>&amp;renditions;</tagsDecl></encodingDesc></teiHeader><text><body><entry xml:id="entry_cʼærna" xml:lang="os-x-digor"><form type="lemma"><orth>cʼærna</orth></form><usg><lang/></usg><sense><sense><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>веснущатый</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>freckled</q></tr></sense><sense><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>пятнистый</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>spotted</q></tr></sense><sense><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>веснушка</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>freckle</q></tr></sense></sense><re><form type="lemma"><orth>cʼærna karkæ</orth></form><sense><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>рябая курица</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>speckled hen</q></tr></sense></re><re><form type="lemma"><orth>cærnagun</orth></form><sense><sense><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>рябой</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>specky</q></tr></sense><sense><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>веснущатый</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>freckled</q></tr></sense></sense></re><etym xml:lang="ru">Примыкает к <mentioned xml:lang="ka"><lang/> <w>cʼreli</w></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="ka"><w>č’rela</w> <gloss><q>пестрый</q></gloss></mentioned>,  через ступени %ičʼrela → *cʼærla → cʼærna%i, ср. звуковые отношения <mentioned xml:lang="ka"><lang/> <w>cxrila</w></mentioned> → ос. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_syxyrna"/> ‘решето’. Огласовка %iæ%i в осетинском позволяет рассматривать это слово как „мегрелизм“, хотя в современном мегрельском мы имеем, как и в грузинском, <mentioned xml:lang=""><lang/> <w>čʼreli</w></mentioned>, а не %i*čʼrali%i (ср. „мегрельскую“ огласовку в %ikær%i-, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_car"/>). Грузинское слово, со своей стороны, можно поставить в связь с некоторыми словами других кавказских языков: <mentioned xml:lang="lez"><lang/> <w>cʼarù</w> <gloss><q>пестрый</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="tab"><lang/> <w>cʼar-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="av"><lang/> <w>čar-</w></mentioned> id.%n<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>526</biblScope></bibl>.</etym><etym xml:lang="en">It relates to <mentioned xml:lang="ka"><lang/> <w>cʼreli</w></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="ka"><w>č’rela</w> <gloss><q>mottle</q></gloss></mentioned>,  through the following steps: %ičʼrela → *cʼærla → cʼærna%i, cf. sound relations <mentioned xml:lang="ka"><lang/> <w>cxrila</w></mentioned> → Ossetic. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_syxyrna"/> ‘sieve’. The vocalization %iæ%i in Ossetic let consider this word as a “Mingrelism”, although in modern Mingrelian, as well as in Georgian, we have <mentioned xml:lang=""><lang/> <w>čʼreli</w></mentioned>, and not %i*čʼrali%i (cf. “Mingrelian” vocalization in %ikær%i-, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_car"/>). The Georgian word, for its part, can be related to some words of other Caucasian languages: <mentioned xml:lang="lez"><lang/> <w>cʼarù</w> <gloss><q>mottle</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="tab"><lang/> <w>cʼar-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="av"><lang/> <w>čar-</w></mentioned> id.%n<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>526</biblScope></bibl>.</etym></entry></body></text></TEI>